rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be placed on any bunny which dies immediately. All bunnies within three spaces are also killed. Horseshoe bunnies may survive.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be placed on any one bunny which is abducted by the Beyea Aliens. The bunny is returned when another is taken.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text:
If an abducted bunny has any Bunny Modifier cards (such as Clover or the Containment Suit), or a pending card (such as a Feed The Bunny card, The Trojan Bunny or The Ebola Virus), then those cards are immediately discarded.

If the bunny that is abducted has Cyber Bunny on top of it, then the bunny goes away with the Beyea Aliens and Cyber Bunny moves on to the next viable bunny target in The Bunny Circle.

A player with an abducted bunny and no other bunny in The Bunny Circle may not play any Aggressive cards (cards that have a Pink rectangular box) or a Choose A Carrot card. An abducted bunny cannot count towards a Bunny Triplet because it is not in The Bunny Circle. At the end of the game, a player with only an abducted bunny may still win the game (since the bunny is still alive).

rules.title: Hitchbunny's Guide
rules.text: Hitchbunny's Guide can be used to retrieve this card from the discard pile because it contains a picture of the planet Jupiter.

rules.title: Bunnies In Black
rules.text: Bunnies In Black can be used to protect a player's bunnies from abduction, or used to return all abducted bunnies.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to throw this card into the air and to take any one opponent's entire Radish and Milk supply if the card lands Butter Side Up.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player and given to any opponent who must sacrifice any one of his bunnies in The Bunny Circle before he may play an Aggressive card.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Dead Zone may be given to an opponent who has no bunnies.

rules.title: Aggressive Cards
rules.text: All cards that have a Pink rectangular box on the left border of the card are considered to be Aggressive cards with the exception of Choose A Carrot (any amount of Carrots) cards.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once to force all players to rotate one of their bunnies to the next player counter-clockwise. Players without bunnies do not participate.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Each player may choose which of his bunnies to rotate.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player as a bunny of any kind and any color (except Red or Pink).

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Free Agent bunny may be used by a player as any bunny of any kind (Evil, Hypnotic, Ludicrous, Spiffy and Truculent) and any color (except Red or Pink). The identity of the bunny may change at any time during play as the need arises. Free Agent bunnies make forming a Bunny Triplet much easier. Free Agent bunnies cannot become Specialty bunnies or Celebrity bunnies.

rules.title: Cloning
rules.text: This bunny cannot be Cloned

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to force any one opponent to either pay 2 Dolla for each or to return a Carrot for each RUN card in his five-card hand.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text:
Reopens the store - New prices:
2 Dolla - for each Radish Card
1 Dolla - for each Milk Card
10 Dolla - for each Carrot

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: CLOSED. Players may still take Carrots using Choose A Carrot cards.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be placed under any bunny. Lucky Horseshoe Quadruple lowers the level of any weapon by four.

rules.title: 50/50 Weapons
rules.text: 50/50 Weapons are not affected by Horseshoe modifiers.

rules.title: Gender Weapons
rules.text: Gender Weapons are not affected by Horseshoe modifiers.

rules.title: Abduction
rules.text: Horseshoe modifiers are discarded when a bunny is abducted by Area 51 or the Mothership.

rules.title: Horseshoes and Hand Grenade
rules.text: Horseshoes and Hand Grenade can be used to kill Horseshoe Bunnies by forcing them to roll higher than their total number of horseshoes to survive.

rules.title: Bamboozled Blacksmith
rules.text: Bamboozled Blacksmith can be used to remove Horseshoes from a bunny.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: Metals may be bought or sold for the current Exchange Rate. All Metal dice may be re-rolled at the end of any turn during which a player received a Carrot. All Gold values are doubled.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to discard any one of his saved Metal cards, add 20 to each of the numbers rolled and steal the Carrots with those numbers from either Kaballa or any opponents.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to rearrange the positions of any one player's bunnies in The Bunny Circle.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Any bunny that has it's position changed must remain the property of the initial owner.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be placed on any bunny. The player rolls the die and the two bunnies the same number of spaces away in The Bunny Circle as the number rolled are immediately killed.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be placed under any bunny and always makes sure that it has enough food to eat. No Feed The Bunny cards affect this bunny.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Nanny remains under the bunny while it is alive.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to eliminate Angry Beet Farmer or to counteract Sour Hour before losing all of his Milk Units. This card must be a saved Special to be used immediately.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Unlike Very Special cards, Beefed Up Production may not be used to save other players' bunnies from harm. This card is for the exclusive use of the player who has it saved.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to take one Radish Card and one Milk Card from Kaballa's Market Two.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Free Radish And Milk may not be used if Kaballa's Market Two is closed.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to immediately play any weapon card directly from his five-card hand.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to either eliminate Gremlins or to counteract Starving Snails before losing all of his Radish Units. This card must be a saved Special to be used immediately.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: Unlike Very Special cards, Shell Repel may not be used to save other players' bunnies from harm. This card is for the exclusive use of the player who has it saved.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to place any one of his own bunnies from The Bunny Circle off to the side and to return it to The Bunny Circle just before the Magic Carrot is revealed.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: While off to the side, the bunny may not be attacked, made to feed, or be abducted by any opponent. A player with only this bunny may not play Aggressive cards.

rules.title: Aggressive Cards
rules.text: All cards that have a Pink rectangular box on the left border of the card are considered to be Aggressive cards with the exception of Choose A Carrot (any amount of Carrots) cards.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once to force all players to rotate their Top Run card to the next player clockwise

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to force any one opponent to return a Carrot to Kaballa's Market Two when his phone makes any type of noise (ring, vibration, bleep, etc.). May be used at any time!

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to immediately force any one opponent to discard all of the weapon cards in his five-card hand and those being played during the current turn. May be used at any time!

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: The opponent must immediately draw new cards from the Draw Pile.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: May be used once by a player to redirect any Feed The Bunny card placed on any bunny onto any other bunny. May be used at any time!

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: Without giving any thought to an exit strategy, one of your bunnies flippantly insults 300 Spartan warriors.

rules.title: Additional Rules
rules.text: If a player draws a PLAY IMMEDIATELY card but has no bunny in The Bunny Circle, then he must place the card on an opponent's bunny in The Bunny Circle causing it to die (discarded). This is also true if the player's only bunny in The Bunny Circle is protected by The Heavenly Halo or Angel Wings.

rules.title: Protection
rules.text: The Heavenly Halo and Angel Wings will protect a bunny from any terrible misfortune. The Guardian Angle can be used to eliminate a Terrible Misfortune.

rules.title: Card Text
rules.text: While quenching his thirst for adventure, one of your bunnies attempts to fly with wax wings on a far too sunny day!
